name: Casualty of Coincidences
description: The coincidences make us, and make our way. I think of everything I am, what I am not and how different I could have been if it weren't for a small detail, some tiny decision that I was about to not make or anything else that I never got to do. Anyway, when you look back you see everything that led you to this place and you start to think about why this or that happened, about the processes behind what apparently was just chance, because the fact that something is new and unknown does not mean that it is a simple coincidence without cause.
